<eesti> ______ (1) K&auml;esolev direktiiv on liikmesriikidele teatavaks tehtud 3. detsembril 1984. </eesti>
<inglise> ANNEX </inglise>
<eesti> LISA </eesti>
<inglise> SPECIMEN AGREEMENT </inglise>
<eesti> N&Auml;IDISLEPING </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Scope </inglise>
<eesti> Reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise> The object of this Agreement is to regulate the reciprocal obligations of export credit insurers of the European Economic Community in cases where: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva lepingu eesm&auml;rgiks on reguleerida Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse ekspordikrediidikindlustuse andjate vastastikuseid kohustusi j&auml;rgmistel juhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise> - an undertaking (hereinafter called'the principal contractor') subcontracts to one or more undertakings (hereinafter called'the subcontractors') of one or more Member States of the European Economic Community an export contract of which the principal contractor is the sole holder, and which it has concluded with an undertaking (hereinafter called'the buyer') situated: </inglise>
<eesti> - ettev&otilde;tja (edaspidi "peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja") s&otilde;lmib &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme ettev&otilde;tjaga (edaspidi "allhankija") &uuml;hes v&otilde;i mitmes Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse liikmesriigis enda nimel ekspordilepingu ettev&otilde;tjaga (edaspidi "ostja"), kes asub: </eesti>
<inglise> - either in a country not belonging to the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> - kas riigis, mis ei kuulu Euroopa Majandus&uuml;hendusse, </eesti>
<inglise> - or in a Member State of the European Economic Community other than those in which the principal contractor and the subcontractor(s) are situated; </inglise>
<eesti> - v&otilde;i Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse liikmesriigis, v&auml;lja arvatud peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja ja allhankija(te) asukohaliikmesriik; </eesti>
<inglise> - the principal contractor has undertaken to remit to the subcontractor(s) the portion due to the latter out of the sums paid by the buyer to the principal contractor, and to complete any formalities which may be necessary to transfer that portion of the payments made by the buyer which is due to the subcontractor(s); </inglise>
<eesti> - peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja kohustub kandma allhankijale v&otilde;i allhankijatele &uuml;le talle v&otilde;i neile kuuluva summa ostja poolt peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tjale makstavatest summadest ning t&auml;itma k&otilde;ik vormin&otilde;uded, mida on vaja ostja poolt makstud ning allhankijale v&otilde;i allhankijatele kuuluva summa &uuml;lekandmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> - there are no legal ties between the subcontractor(s) and the buyer; </inglise>
<eesti> - allhankija v&otilde;i allhankijate ja ostja vahel ei ole &otilde;iguslikke suhteid; </eesti>
<inglise> - the principal contractor's credit insurer (hereinafter called'the principal insurer') and the credit insurer(s) of the subcontractor(s) (hereinafter called'the joint insurer(s) ' ) are prepared to guarantee, each according to the usual terms of his policy, the portion of the operation carried out in their respective countries against the risks defined by them in each individual agreement. </inglise>
<eesti> - peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja krediidikindlustusandja (edaspidi "p&otilde;hikindlustusandja") ning allhankija v&otilde;i allhankijate krediidikindlustusandja v&otilde;i krediidikindlustusandjad (edaspidi "kaaskindlustajad") on valmis iga&uuml;ks vastavalt oma tavap&auml;rastele kindlustustingimustele kindlustama tema riigis toimuva tehingu osa igas &uuml;ksiklepingus m&auml;&auml;ratletud riskide vastu. </eesti>
<inglise> The agreement which the abovementioned export credit insurers shall conclude in each individual case relating to the issue of joint guarantees to a principal contractor and to one or more subcontractors shall be governed by the Articles below. </inglise>
<eesti> Lepinguid, mille eespool nimetatud ekspordikrediidikindlustuse andjad s&otilde;lmivad igal &uuml;ksikjuhul &uuml;hisgarantii andmise kohta peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tjale v&otilde;i &uuml;hele v&otilde;i mitmele allhankijale, reguleerivad j&auml;rgmised artiklid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Obligations of the principal insurer </inglise>
<eesti> P&otilde;hikindlustusandja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise> The principal insurer, being the sole manager of the risk, including the subcontracted element, shall undertake: </inglise>
<eesti> P&otilde;hikindlustusandja, kes vastutab ainuisikuliselt riskijuhtimise, sealhulgas allhankelepingute eest, kohustub: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) to guarantee the principal contractor, in respect only of the latter's part of the contract, against the risks defined by him in each individual agreement; </inglise>
<eesti> a) kindlustama need peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja riskid tema lepinguosa piires, mis on m&auml;&auml;ratletud igas &uuml;ksiklepingus; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) not to accept any modification to any of the terms of performance of the contract (amount, delivery, payment, etc.) or to the contract between the principal contractor and the subcontractor(s) for the performance of that contract, unless mutually agreed with the joint insurer(s); </inglise>
<eesti> b) mitte heaks kiitma muudatusi lepingu t&auml;itmise tingimustes (summa, tarned, maksed jne) v&otilde;i peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja ning allhankija v&otilde;i allhankijate vahel k&otilde;nesoleva lepingu t&auml;itmiseks s&otilde;lmitavas lepingus, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui seda tehakse vastastikusel kokkuleppel kaaskindlustaja v&otilde;i kaaskindlustajatega; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) not to disclaim liability under the provisions of the policy issued to the principal contractor in consequence of any default on the latter's part, without notifying the joint insurer(s) thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> c) mitte loobuma peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tjale v&auml;ljaantud kindlustuspoliisist tulenevatest kohustustest peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja lepinguliste kohustuste t&auml;itmataj&auml;tmisel, ilma et sellest oleks kaaskindlustajale v&otilde;i kaaskindlustajatele teatatud; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) not to declare that the policy has lapsed without notifying the joint insurer(s) thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> d) mitte tunnistama kindlustuspoliisi kehtivust l&otilde;ppenuks, ilma et sellest oleks kaaskindlustajale v&otilde;i kaaskindlustajatele teatatud; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) to notify to the joint insurer(s) any fact which comes to his knowledge and which might alter the nature or extent of the risk or lead to a loss; </inglise>
<eesti> e) teatama kaaskindlustajale v&otilde;i kaaskindlustajatele k&otilde;igist talle teadaolevatest faktidest, mis v&otilde;ivad muuta riski laadi v&otilde;i suurust v&otilde;i tekitada kahju; </eesti>
<inglise> (f) in the event of loss or threat of loss, to consult the joint insurer(s) on the steps to be taken; decisions to acknowledge a loss shall, so far as possible, be taken by mutual agreement, the amount of the indemnity and the method of payment being fixed in accordance with the provisions of each policy; </inglise>
<eesti> f) kahju v&otilde;i kahjuohu korral pidama kaaskindlustaja v&otilde;i kaaskindlustajatega n&otilde;u v&otilde;etavate meetmete &uuml;le; otsused kahju t&otilde;endamise kohta tehakse v&otilde;imaluse korral vastastikusel kokkuleppel ning h&uuml;vitise suurus ja selle maksmise &uuml;ksikasjad m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks vastavalt iga kindlustuspoliisi tingimustele; </eesti>
<inglise> (g) in the event of a loss, to take the necessary steps or require the principal contractor to take the necessary steps to recover amounts unpaid and to pay back to the joint insurer the portion owed to the latter out of the sums recovered and to complete any necessary formalities for transferring such portion. </inglise>
<eesti> g) kahju korral v&otilde;tma vajalikke meetmeid v&otilde;i n&otilde;udma, et peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;taks vajalikke meetmeid maksmata summade sissen&otilde;udmiseks ja kaaskindlustajale talle kuuluva summa tagasimaksmiseks sissen&otilde;utud summadest, ning t&auml;itma k&otilde;ik sellise summa &uuml;lekandmiseks vajalikud vormin&otilde;uded. </eesti>
<inglise> The costs incurred in recovery by the principal insurer shall be divided between the insurers in proportion to the share of the contract covered; </inglise>
<eesti> P&otilde;hikindlustusandja poolt summade sissen&otilde;udmisel tehtud kulutused jagatakse kindlustusandjate vahel vastavalt nende osale kindlustusega kaetud lepingus; </eesti>
<inglise> (h) in the event of cancellation of the guarantee given to the principal contractor, to use his best endeavours to meet the obligations set out in this Article. </inglise>
<eesti> h) andma endast parima peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tjale antud garantii t&uuml;histamise korral, et t&auml;ita k&auml;esolevas artiklis s&auml;testatud kohustused. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Obligations of each of the joint insurers </inglise>
<eesti> Kaaskindlustaja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise> Each of the joint insurers shall, for his part, undertake: </inglise>
<eesti> Kaaskindlustaja kohustub: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) to guarantee the subcontractor in his country, in respect only of the latter's part of the operation, against the risks defined by him in each individual agreement; </inglise>
<eesti> a) kindlustama need oma riigi allhankija riskid tema tehinguosa piires, mis on m&auml;&auml;ratletud igas &uuml;ksiklepingus; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) not to accept any modification to the contract concluded between the principal contractor and the subcontractor for the performance of the contract concluded with the buyer, except by mutual agreement with the principal insurer; </inglise>
<eesti> b) mitte heaks kiitma muudatusi peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja ja allhankija vahel ostjaga s&otilde;lmitud lepingu t&auml;itmiseks s&otilde;lmitavas lepingus, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui seda tehakse vastastikusel kokkuleppel p&otilde;hikindlustusandjaga; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) not to disclaim liability under the provisions of the policy issued to the subcontractor in consequence of any default on the latter's part, without notifying the principal insurer thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> c) mitte loobuma allhankijale v&auml;ljaantud kindlustuspoliisist tulenevatest kohustustest allhankija lepinguliste kohustuste t&auml;itmataj&auml;tmisel, ilma et sellest oleks p&otilde;hikindlustusandjale teatatud; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) not to declare that the policy has lapsed without notifying the principal insurer thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> d) mitte tunnistama kindlustuspoliisi kehtivust l&otilde;ppenuks, ilma et sellest oleks p&otilde;hikindlustusandjale teatatud; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) to notify the principal insurer of any fact which comes to his knowledge and which might alter the nature or extent of the risk or lead to a loss; </inglise>
<eesti> e) teatama p&otilde;hikindlustusandjale k&otilde;igist talle teadaolevatest faktidest, mis v&otilde;ivad muuta riski laadi v&otilde;i suurust v&otilde;i tekitada kahju; </eesti>
<inglise> (f) in the event of cancellation of the guarantee given to the subcontractor, to use his best endeavours to comply with the obligations set out in this Article. </inglise>
<eesti> f) andma endast parima allhankijale antud garantii t&uuml;histamise korral, et t&auml;ita k&auml;esolevas artiklis s&auml;testatud kohustused. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Consolidation </inglise>
<eesti> Konsolidatsioon </eesti>
<inglise> In the vent of agreement to consolidate the debt of the buyer country, the principal insurer and the joint insurer(s) shall hold consultations on ways and means of resolving the specific problems raised by the consolidation agreement. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui s&otilde;lmitakse leping ostjariigi v&otilde;la konsolideerimiseks, peavad p&otilde;hikindlustusandja ning kaaskindlustusandja v&otilde;i kaaskindlustusandjad n&otilde;u, et leida v&otilde;imalused ja vahendid konsolideerimislepingust tulenevate eriprobleemide lahendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Buyer credit operations </inglise>
<eesti> Ostjakrediidil p&otilde;hinevad tehingud </eesti>
<inglise> Those Community credit insurers who agree that their buyer credit systems are sufficiently compatible may further agree to establish or to cover a single buyer credit for the whole of a contract, whereupon the provisions of this Agreement shall apply by analogy. </inglise>
<eesti> Need &uuml;henduse krediidikindlustusandjad, kes on &uuml;hisel arvamusel, et nende ostjakrediidi s&uuml;steemid on piisavalt kokkusobivad, v&otilde;ivad kokku leppida, et kogu lepingu jaoks avatakse &uuml;htne ostjakrediit v&otilde;i kogu leping kaetakse &uuml;htse krediidiga, kusjuures k&auml;esoleva lepingu s&auml;tteid kohaldatakse analoogia alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Arbitration </inglise>
<eesti> Arbitraa&zcaron; </eesti>
<inglise> Any dispute arising out of this Agreement which cannot be settled amicably shall be brought before an arbitration board composed of three arbitrators. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;ik k&auml;esolevast lepingust tulenevad vaidlused, mida ei saa lahendada vastastikusel kokkuleppel, esitatakse kolmest vahekohtunikust koosnevale vahekohtule. </eesti>
<inglise> Each of the parties involved shall appoint one arbitrator. </inglise>
<eesti> Kumbki asjaomane pool nimetab &uuml;he vahekohtuniku. </eesti>
<inglise> The third arbitrator shall be appointed by the President of the Court of Justice of the European Communities; he shall act as chairman of the Arbitration Board. </inglise>
<eesti> Kolmanda vahekohtuniku nimetab Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Kohtu president; tema on vahekohtu esimees. </eesti>
<inglise> The proceedings shall be governed by the Rules of Conciliation and Arbitration of the International Chamber of Commerce. </inglise>
<eesti> Menetlusi reguleerivad Rahvusvahelise Kaubanduskoja lepitus- ja arbitraa&zcaron;ireeglid. </eesti>
 